<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Range burner ignition diagnostic</p>
    <h2>Architecture matters: open burner, hot-top, even-heat plate. Different diagnostic per architecture.</h2>

    <p>Commercial range burner-not-igniting failures depend on the range architecture. <strong>Open-burner ranges</strong> (most common, Vulcan VR / Garland Master M / Imperial IRGB / Wolf Challenger Commercial / Montague Legend / South Bend) have individual visible burners with their own pilot or spark plus gas valve per station; failures are station-specific. <strong>Hot-top ranges</strong> (Vulcan VHP, Garland Sentry HT) have a thick steel plate with an under-plate burner cluster; failures present as the whole hot-top failing or specific zones cooling. <strong>Even-heat plate ranges</strong> (Vulcan VEH, Garland Master EH) use sophisticated zone-controlled burners under an engineered plate; failures present similarly to hot-top but with zone diagnostics on the control board.</p>

    <p>For range with integrated charbroiler module see our <a href="/commercial/charbroiler-repair/burner-not-lighting/">charbroiler burner-not-lighting page</a> (same diagnostic). For commercial standalone oven (separate equipment from range with integrated oven) see <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/">commercial oven repair</a>.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/range-repair/">commercial range repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Field observations</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top causes by frequency.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Pilot cluster thermocouple weak (year 4-7).</strong> Single most common open-burner failure. Adjacent burners served by same pilot cluster fail together. $220-340 thermocouple replacement at cluster level.</li>
      <li><strong>Spark module / spark electrode failure (electronic ignition, year 5-8).</strong> Click but no spark, or spark but no flame. $260-440.</li>
      <li><strong>Pilot orifice carbon clog (year 3-5 standing-pilot models).</strong> $120-200 cleaning service.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas valve safety lockout.</strong> Electronic state after 3 failed ignition attempts. $120 reset only.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas valve mechanical failure (year 7+).</strong> $480-680 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Hot-top / even-heat plate under-plate burner failure.</strong> $480-880 plate-element repair scope.</li>
      <li><strong>Range-top master gas valve safety (whole range top dead).</strong> $120 reset to $480 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas pressure inconsistency across manifold.</strong> $200-600 regulator-side fix.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Diagnostic walkthrough</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Practitioner sequence.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Identify range architecture.</strong> Open burner vs hot-top vs even-heat plate. Determines diagnostic path and access method.</li>
      <li><strong>Identify failure scope.</strong> Single burner, cluster pattern (2-3 adjacent burners on same pilot), or whole range top.</li>
      <li><strong>Verify gas supply at unit.</strong> Isolation valve open, manometer at inlet under load.</li>
      <li><strong>Pilot or spark visual test (open-burner).</strong> Pilot flame strength and steadiness, or spark visible at electrode.</li>
      <li><strong>Multimeter thermocouple under flame (standing pilot).</strong> Voltage output during pilot.</li>
      <li><strong>Plate removal for hot-top / even-heat (if architecture).</strong> Access under-plate burner cluster for visual inspection and test.</li>
      <li><strong>Master gas valve and master ignition module test (whole range top failure).</strong> Continuity, solenoid actuation, control board output.</li>
      <li><strong>Combustion quality verification.</strong> Blue flame steady at all firing burners.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Honest opinion</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Pilot cluster diagnostic is the difference between 1-visit and 3-visit repair.</h2>
    <p>About 60 percent of "won't light" calls on commercial ranges in LA come from pilot cluster thermocouple weakness, not single-burner failure. The mistake we see other shops make: replace the visible burner that "won't light," fail to identify that adjacent burners are also weakening, customer calls back 2 weeks later when the next burner in the cluster fails. We identify the pilot cluster pattern at the first visit and quote cluster-level thermocouple replacement (one truck visit, $220 to $340 vs three truck visits at $660 to $1,020). The cluster-level approach saves the customer money and is what an honest practitioner would recommend.</p>
  </div>
</section>

